cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with improving depth map prediction from monocular images, which is a common problem in computer vision. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as accurate depth estimation is important for robots to navigate and interact with their environment. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes a learning-based approach to predict displacement fields for sharper reconstructions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a method to improve object recognition by improving occlusion boundaries. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with image reconstruction and improving the visual quality of depth maps.
